{"word":"H5117 - נוּחַ - nûwach - noo'-akh - Cease","slug":"H5117","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נוּחַ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nûwach"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>noo'-akh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cease"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05D7; - nu&#x0302;ach</b> - <i>noo'-akh</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>rest</i>, that is, <i>settle</i> down; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively, intransitively, transitively and causatively (to <i>dwell</i>, <i>stay</i>, <i>let fall</i>, <i>place</i>, <i>let alone</i>, <i>withdraw</i>, <i>give comfort</i>, etc.): - cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare <a href=\"#/H3241\">H3241</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2010\">H2010</a>, <a href=\"#/H2679\">H2679</a>, <a href=\"#/H2680\">H2680</a>, <a href=\"#/H3239\">H3239</a>, <a href=\"#/H3240\">H3240</a>, <a href=\"#/H4494\">H4494</a>, <a href=\"#/H4495\">H4495</a>, <a href=\"#/H4496\">H4496</a>, <a href=\"#/H4506\">H4506</a>, <a href=\"#/H5118\">H5118</a>, <a href=\"#/H5119\">H5119</a>, <a href=\"#/H5146\">H5146</a>, <a href=\"#/H5183\">H5183</a>, <a href=\"#/H5207\">H5207</a>"}]}